

1. What is JavaScript?

JavaScript is a programming language of the web.

It adds interactivity to HTML & CSS (which are otherwise static).

Example: Buttons that respond, forms that validate, animations, etc.

üëâ Without JS ‚Üí websites are just ‚Äúread-only‚Äù.
üëâ With JS ‚Üí websites can ‚Äúreact‚Äù to users.

2. Why Use JavaScript? (Advantages)

Runs directly in the browser, no extra setup.

Makes websites dynamic and interactive.

Works with HTML & CSS easily.

Used everywhere ‚Üí frontend (browser) + backend (Node.js).

Huge community + frameworks (React, Angular, Vue).

3. How to Write JavaScript?
Two main ways:

Inline / Internal ‚Üí inside <script> tag in HTML.

External ‚Üí linking .js file with <script src="file.js"></script>.



//-------------------------------------------------------------


üîπ ES5 vs ES6 (Simplified Explanation)

ES = ECMAScript = Official standard of JavaScript.

ES5 (2009) ‚Üí Older version (still supported everywhere).

ES6 (2015) ‚Üí Big upgrade, modern syntax (default in teaching now).



| Feature   | ES5                        | ES6                                  |
| --------- | -------------------------- | ------------------------------------ |
| Variable  | `var`                      | `let`, `const` (better scoping)      |
| Functions | `function myFunc() {}`     | Arrow functions `() => {}`           |
| Strings   | `"Hello " + name`          | Template literals \`Hello \${name}\` |
| Loops     | `for (var i=0; i<10; i++)` | `for...of`, `for...in`               |
| Objects   | Normal only                | Classes & Modules supported          |


